.\" Manpage for gen-changelog
.TH man 1 "24 November 2025" "202602020740-git" "gen-changelog"

.SH NAME
gen-changelog \- Generate CHANGELOG.md from git history

.SH DESCRIPTION
A powerful changelog generation tool that creates and maintains CHANGELOG.md files from git commit history. Supports tag-based organization, commit filtering, and multiple output formats.

.SH SYNOPSIS
gen-changelog [options] [command]

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-init
Create initial empty CHANGELOG.md file
.TP
.B \-\-create
Generate full CHANGELOG.md from entire git history organized by tags
.TP
.B \-\-amend
Amend last commit with changelog changes
.TP
.B \-\-message <MSG>
Set commit message for all file changes
.TP
.B \-\-icon <ICON>
Change default icon (default: ðŸš€)
.TP
.B \-\-files <FILES>
Specify files to include in changelog
.TP
.B \-\-dir <DIR>
Set working directory (default: current directory)
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display comprehensive help message
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display current version information
.TP
.B \-\-config
Generate user configuration file
.TP
.B \-\-options
Show all available options
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debugging output
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Remove all formatting and colors from output

.SH ADVANCED OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-major
Bump major version (X.0.0)
.TP
.B \-\-minor
Bump minor version (0.X.0)
.TP
.B \-\-patch
Bump patch version (0.0.X)
.TP
.B \-\-version-bump
Auto-detect version bump type
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
Select files interactively
.TP
.B \-\-categorize
Group changes by category
.TP
.B \-\-conventional
Parse conventional commit messages
.TP
.B \-\-format <FORMAT>
Output format: markdown, json, yaml, html (default: markdown)
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Show changelog statistics
.TP
.B \-\-release
Generate release notes from git history
.TP
.B \-\-since-tag <TAG>
Show changes since specific tag
.TP
.B \-\-author
Include commit authors in changelog
.TP
.B \-\-contributors
List all contributors
.TP
.B \-\-pr <NUMBER>
Link to pull request
.TP
.B \-\-issue <NUMBER>
Link to issue
.TP
.B \-\-link-commits
Add commit links to entries
.TP
.B \-\-github-url <URL>
Set GitHub repository URL for links
.TP
.B \-\-undo
Undo last changelog update

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B gen-changelog \-\-create
Generate complete CHANGELOG.md from entire git history
.TP
.B gen-changelog \-\-message "Added feature" \-\-files "file1.sh file2.txt"
Add changelog entry for specific files
.TP
.B gen-changelog \-\-release
Generate release notes from git history
.TP
.B gen-changelog \-\-since-tag v1.0.0
Show changes since version 1.0.0
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_EXCLUDE_PATTERN="Merge|WIP" gen-changelog \-\-create
Create changelog excluding merge commits and WIP commits
.TP
.B gen-changelog \-\-categorize \-\-conventional
Generate categorized changelog using conventional commits

.SH CHANGELOG FORMAT
The \-\-create flag generates a detailed changelog with the following structure:
.TP
.B Tag Sections
Each git tag creates a section with date: ## [v1.0.0] - 2024-11-24
.TP
.B Unreleased Section
Commits after the latest tag appear under ## [Unreleased]
.TP
.B Commit Details
Each commit shows:
.br
- Subject as H3 header (### Subject)
.br
- Metadata: Commit hash | Author | Date
.br
- Full commit body with file changes

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_EXCLUDE_PATTERN
Pipe-separated regex patterns to exclude from changelog (default: "Version Bump:"). Example: "Version Bump:|Merge|fixup|WIP"
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_FILE_NAME
Name of changelog file (default: CHANGELOG)
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_FILE_EXT
Changelog file extension (default: md)
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_DEFAULT_ICON
Default icon for entries (default: ðŸš€)
.TP
.B GEN_CHANGELOG_VERSION_FILE
Version file name (default: version.txt)

